---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const lastUpdated = new Date("2026-02-09"); // update when you edit
const daysOld = Math.floor((Date.now() - lastUpdated.getTime()) / 86400000);
const isStale = daysOld > 180; // 6 months

---

<BaseLayout title="Now">
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-10 space-y-6">
    <h1 class="text-xl font-medium">Now</h1>

    <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">
      What I'm up to as of {lastUpdated.toLocaleDateString("en-US", { year: "numeric", month: "long" })}
      {isStale && " · (I hope this note is aging gracefully.)"}
      {isStale && (
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">
          If this note feels out of date, you can <a class="underline" href="/ping">ping me</a>.
        </p>
      )}
    </p>

    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
      This is a small snapshot of where I'm at lately.
      There's no schedule for updating it; I change it when it no longer feels true.
    </p>

    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
      Right now, I'm learning, experimenting, and building this site slowly.
      I'm trying to let curiosity lead, instead of worrying too much about polish
      or having everything figured out. That's hard for me! 
    </p>

    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
      I've been thinking a lot about creativity and community. Making things
      and sharing them. 
      I'm practicing showing up honestly, even when things are unfinished.
    </p>

    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
      If you're reading this, thanks for being here.
      Wherever you are in your own process, I hope you're being gentle with yourself.
    </p>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
